The evidence with the title 'Five myths about the 47 percent - The Washington Post ' says Sep 21, 2012  ... Forty-seven percent of Americans don't pay taxes.  ... And their payroll taxes help finance Social Security and Medicare.  ... And those aren't the only other taxes they bear.  ... About half of these households don't pay federal income tax simply because their incomes are low.  ... The 47 percent vote Democratic. 
